67struct hb_closure_context_t :
68 hb_dispatch_context_t<hb_closure_context_t>
69{
70 typedef return_t (*recurse_func_t) (hb_closure_context_t *c, unsigned lookup_index, hb_set_t *covered_seq_indicies, unsigned seq_index, unsigned end_index);
71 template <typename T>
72 return_t dispatch (const T &obj) { obj.closure (this); return hb_empty_t (); }
73 static return_t default_return_value () { return hb_empty_t (); }
74 void recurse (unsigned lookup_index, hb_set_t *covered_seq_indicies, unsigned seq_index, unsigned end_index)
75 {
76 if (unlikely (nesting_level_left == 0 || !recurse_func))
77 return;
78
79 nesting_level_left--;
80 recurse_func (this, lookup_index, covered_seq_indicies, seq_index, end_index);
81 nesting_level_left++;
82 }
83
84 void reset_lookup_visit_count ()
85 { lookup_count = 0; }
86
87 bool lookup_limit_exceeded ()
88 { return lookup_count > HB_MAX_LOOKUP_VISIT_COUNT; }
89
90 bool should_visit_lookup (unsigned int lookup_index)
91 {
92 if (lookup_count++ > HB_MAX_LOOKUP_VISIT_COUNT)
93 return false;
94
95 if (is_lookup_done (lookup_index))
96 return false;
97
98 return true;
99 }
100
101 bool is_lookup_done (unsigned int lookup_index)
102 {
103 if (unlikely (done_lookups_glyph_count->in_error () ||
104 done_lookups_glyph_set->in_error ()))
105 return true;
106
107 /* Have we visited this lookup with the current set of glyphs? */
108 if (done_lookups_glyph_count->get (key: lookup_index) != glyphs->get_population ())
109 {
110 done_lookups_glyph_count->set (key: lookup_index, value: glyphs->get_population ());
111
112 if (!done_lookups_glyph_set->has (key: lookup_index))
113 {
114 if (unlikely (!done_lookups_glyph_set->set (lookup_index, hb::unique_ptr<hb_set_t> {hb_set_create ()})))
115 return true;
116 }
117
118 done_lookups_glyph_set->get (key: lookup_index)->clear ();
119 }
120
121 hb_set_t *covered_glyph_set = done_lookups_glyph_set->get (key: lookup_index);
122 if (unlikely (covered_glyph_set->in_error ()))
123 return true;
124 if (parent_active_glyphs ().is_subset (larger_set: *covered_glyph_set))
125 return true;
126
127 covered_glyph_set->union_ (other: parent_active_glyphs ());
128 return false;
129 }
130
131 const hb_set_t& previous_parent_active_glyphs () {
132 if (active_glyphs_stack.length <= 1)
133 return *glyphs;
134
135 return active_glyphs_stack[active_glyphs_stack.length - 2];
136 }
137
138 const hb_set_t& parent_active_glyphs ()
139 {
140 if (!active_glyphs_stack)
141 return *glyphs;
142
143 return active_glyphs_stack.tail ();
144 }
145
146 hb_set_t& push_cur_active_glyphs ()
147 {
148 return *active_glyphs_stack.push ();
149 }
150
151 bool pop_cur_done_glyphs ()
152 {
153 if (!active_glyphs_stack)
154 return false;
155
156 active_glyphs_stack.pop ();
157 return true;
158 }
159
160 hb_face_t *face;
161 hb_set_t *glyphs;
162 hb_set_t output[1];
163 hb_vector_t<hb_set_t> active_glyphs_stack;
164 recurse_func_t recurse_func = nullptr;
165 unsigned int nesting_level_left;
166
167 hb_closure_context_t (hb_face_t *face_,
168 hb_set_t *glyphs_,
169 hb_map_t *done_lookups_glyph_count_,
170 hb_hashmap_t<unsigned, hb::unique_ptr<hb_set_t>> *done_lookups_glyph_set_,
171 unsigned int nesting_level_left_ = HB_MAX_NESTING_LEVEL) :
172 face (face_),
173 glyphs (glyphs_),
174 nesting_level_left (nesting_level_left_),
175 done_lookups_glyph_count (done_lookups_glyph_count_),
176 done_lookups_glyph_set (done_lookups_glyph_set_)
177 {}
178
179 ~hb_closure_context_t () { flush (); }
180
181 void set_recurse_func (recurse_func_t func) { recurse_func = func; }
182
183 void flush ()
184 {
185 output->del_range (a: face->get_num_glyphs (), HB_SET_VALUE_INVALID); /* Remove invalid glyphs. */
186 glyphs->union_ (other: *output);
187 output->clear ();
188 active_glyphs_stack.pop ();
189 active_glyphs_stack.reset ();
190 }
191
192 private:
193 hb_map_t *done_lookups_glyph_count;
194 hb_hashmap_t<unsigned, hb::unique_ptr<hb_set_t>> *done_lookups_glyph_set;
195 unsigned int lookup_count = 0;
196};

200struct hb_closure_lookups_context_t :
201 hb_dispatch_context_t<hb_closure_lookups_context_t>
202{
203 typedef return_t (*recurse_func_t) (hb_closure_lookups_context_t *c, unsigned lookup_index);
204 template <typename T>
205 return_t dispatch (const T &obj) { obj.closure_lookups (this); return hb_empty_t (); }
206 static return_t default_return_value () { return hb_empty_t (); }
207 void recurse (unsigned lookup_index)
208 {
209 if (unlikely (nesting_level_left == 0 || !recurse_func))
210 return;
211
212 /* Return if new lookup was recursed to before. */
213 if (lookup_limit_exceeded ()
214 || visited_lookups->in_error ()
215 || visited_lookups->has (k: lookup_index))
216 // Don't increment lookup count here, that will be done in the call to closure_lookups()
217 // made by recurse_func.
218 return;
219
220 nesting_level_left--;
221 recurse_func (this, lookup_index);
222 nesting_level_left++;
223 }
224
225 void set_lookup_visited (unsigned lookup_index)
226 { visited_lookups->add (g: lookup_index); }
227
228 void set_lookup_inactive (unsigned lookup_index)
229 { inactive_lookups->add (g: lookup_index); }
230
231 bool lookup_limit_exceeded ()
232 {
233 bool ret = lookup_count > HB_MAX_LOOKUP_VISIT_COUNT;
234 if (ret)
235 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "lookup visit count limit exceeded in lookup closure!");
236 return ret; }
237
238 bool is_lookup_visited (unsigned lookup_index)
239 {
240 if (unlikely (lookup_count++ > HB_MAX_LOOKUP_VISIT_COUNT))
241 {
242 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "total visited lookup count %u exceeds max limit, lookup %u is dropped.",
243 lookup_count, lookup_index);
244 return true;
245 }
246
247 if (unlikely (visited_lookups->in_error ()))
248 return true;
249
250 return visited_lookups->has (k: lookup_index);
251 }
252
253 hb_face_t *face;
254 const hb_set_t *glyphs;
255 recurse_func_t recurse_func;
256 unsigned int nesting_level_left;
257
258 hb_closure_lookups_context_t (hb_face_t *face_,
259 const hb_set_t *glyphs_,
260 hb_set_t *visited_lookups_,
261 hb_set_t *inactive_lookups_,
262 unsigned nesting_level_left_ = HB_MAX_NESTING_LEVEL) :
263 face (face_),
264 glyphs (glyphs_),
265 recurse_func (nullptr),
266 nesting_level_left (nesting_level_left_),
267 visited_lookups (visited_lookups_),
268 inactive_lookups (inactive_lookups_),
269 lookup_count (0) {}
270
271 void set_recurse_func (recurse_func_t func) { recurse_func = func; }
272
273 private:
274 hb_set_t *visited_lookups;
275 hb_set_t *inactive_lookups;
276 unsigned int lookup_count;
277};

302struct hb_collect_glyphs_context_t :
303 hb_dispatch_context_t<hb_collect_glyphs_context_t>
304{
305 typedef return_t (*recurse_func_t) (hb_collect_glyphs_context_t *c, unsigned int lookup_index);
306 template <typename T>
307 return_t dispatch (const T &obj) { obj.collect_glyphs (this); return hb_empty_t (); }
308 static return_t default_return_value () { return hb_empty_t (); }
309 void recurse (unsigned int lookup_index)
310 {
311 if (unlikely (nesting_level_left == 0 || !recurse_func))
312 return;
313
314 /* Note that GPOS sets recurse_func to nullptr already, so it doesn't get
315 * past the previous check. For GSUB, we only want to collect the output
316 * glyphs in the recursion. If output is not requested, we can go home now.
317 *
318 * Note further, that the above is not exactly correct. A recursed lookup
319 * is allowed to match input that is not matched in the context, but that's
320 * not how most fonts are built. It's possible to relax that and recurse
321 * with all sets here if it proves to be an issue.
322 */
323
324 if (output == hb_set_get_empty ())
325 return;
326
327 /* Return if new lookup was recursed to before. */
328 if (recursed_lookups->has (k: lookup_index))
329 return;
330
331 hb_set_t *old_before = before;
332 hb_set_t *old_input = input;
333 hb_set_t *old_after = after;
334 before = input = after = hb_set_get_empty ();
335
336 nesting_level_left--;
337 recurse_func (this, lookup_index);
338 nesting_level_left++;
339
340 before = old_before;
341 input = old_input;
342 after = old_after;
343
344 recursed_lookups->add (g: lookup_index);
345 }
346
347 hb_face_t *face;
348 hb_set_t *before;
349 hb_set_t *input;
350 hb_set_t *after;
351 hb_set_t *output;
352 recurse_func_t recurse_func;
353 hb_set_t *recursed_lookups;
354 unsigned int nesting_level_left;
355
356 hb_collect_glyphs_context_t (hb_face_t *face_,
357 hb_set_t *glyphs_before, /* OUT. May be NULL */
358 hb_set_t *glyphs_input, /* OUT. May be NULL */
359 hb_set_t *glyphs_after, /* OUT. May be NULL */
360 hb_set_t *glyphs_output, /* OUT. May be NULL */
361 unsigned int nesting_level_left_ = HB_MAX_NESTING_LEVEL) :
362 face (face_),
363 before (glyphs_before ? glyphs_before : hb_set_get_empty ()),
364 input (glyphs_input ? glyphs_input : hb_set_get_empty ()),
365 after (glyphs_after ? glyphs_after : hb_set_get_empty ()),
366 output (glyphs_output ? glyphs_output : hb_set_get_empty ()),
367 recurse_func (nullptr),
368 recursed_lookups (hb_set_create ()),
369 nesting_level_left (nesting_level_left_) {}
370 ~hb_collect_glyphs_context_t () { hb_set_destroy (set: recursed_lookups); }
371
372 void set_recurse_func (recurse_func_t func) { recurse_func = func; }
373};

397struct hb_ot_apply_context_t :
398 hb_dispatch_context_t<hb_ot_apply_context_t, bool, HB_DEBUG_APPLY>
399{
400 struct matcher_t
401 {
402 matcher_t () :
403 lookup_props (0),
404 mask (-1),
405 ignore_zwnj (false),
406 ignore_zwj (false),
407 per_syllable (false),
408 syllable {0},
409 match_func (nullptr),
410 match_data (nullptr) {}
411
412 typedef bool (*match_func_t) (hb_glyph_info_t &info, unsigned value, const void *data);
413
414 void set_ignore_zwnj (bool ignore_zwnj_) { ignore_zwnj = ignore_zwnj_; }
415 void set_ignore_zwj (bool ignore_zwj_) { ignore_zwj = ignore_zwj_; }
416 void set_lookup_props (unsigned int lookup_props_) { lookup_props = lookup_props_; }
417 void set_mask (hb_mask_t mask_) { mask = mask_; }
418 void set_per_syllable (bool per_syllable_) { per_syllable = per_syllable_; }
419 void set_syllable (uint8_t syllable_) { syllable = per_syllable ? syllable_ : 0; }
420 void set_match_func (match_func_t match_func_,
421 const void *match_data_)
422 { match_func = match_func_; match_data = match_data_; }
423
424 enum may_match_t {
425 MATCH_NO,
426 MATCH_YES,
427 MATCH_MAYBE
428 };
429
430 may_match_t may_match (hb_glyph_info_t &info,
431 hb_codepoint_t glyph_data) const
432 {
433 if (!(info.mask & mask) ||
434 (syllable && syllable != info.syllable ()))
435 return MATCH_NO;
436
437 if (match_func)
438 return match_func (info, glyph_data, match_data) ? MATCH_YES : MATCH_NO;
439
440 return MATCH_MAYBE;
441 }
442
443 enum may_skip_t {
444 SKIP_NO,
445 SKIP_YES,
446 SKIP_MAYBE
447 };
448
449 may_skip_t may_skip (const hb_ot_apply_context_t *c,
450 const hb_glyph_info_t &info) const
451 {
452 if (!c->check_glyph_property (info: &info, match_props: lookup_props))
453 return SKIP_YES;
454
455 if (unlikely (_hb_glyph_info_is_default_ignorable_and_not_hidden (&info) &&
456 (ignore_zwnj || !_hb_glyph_info_is_zwnj (&info)) &&
457 (ignore_zwj || !_hb_glyph_info_is_zwj (&info))))
458 return SKIP_MAYBE;
459
460 return SKIP_NO;
461 }
462
463 protected:
464 unsigned int lookup_props;
465 hb_mask_t mask;
466 bool ignore_zwnj;
467 bool ignore_zwj;
468 bool per_syllable;
469 uint8_t syllable;
470 match_func_t match_func;
471 const void *match_data;
472 };
473
474 struct skipping_iterator_t
475 {
476 void init (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c_, bool context_match = false)
477 {
478 c = c_;
479 match_glyph_data16 = nullptr;
480#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
481 match_glyph_data24 = nullptr;
482#endif
483 matcher.set_match_func (match_func_: nullptr, match_data_: nullptr);
484 matcher.set_lookup_props (c->lookup_props);
485 /* Ignore ZWNJ if we are matching GPOS, or matching GSUB context and asked to. */
486 matcher.set_ignore_zwnj (c->table_index == 1 || (context_match && c->auto_zwnj));
487 /* Ignore ZWJ if we are matching context, or asked to. */
488 matcher.set_ignore_zwj (context_match || c->auto_zwj);
489 matcher.set_mask (context_match ? -1 : c->lookup_mask);
490 matcher.set_per_syllable (c->per_syllable);
491 }
492 void set_lookup_props (unsigned int lookup_props)
493 {
494 matcher.set_lookup_props (lookup_props);
495 }
496 void set_match_func (matcher_t::match_func_t match_func_,
497 const void *match_data_)
498 {
499 matcher.set_match_func (match_func_, match_data_);
500 }
501 void set_glyph_data (const HBUINT16 glyph_data[])
502 {
503 match_glyph_data16 = glyph_data;
504#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
505 match_glyph_data24 = nullptr;
506#endif
507 }
508#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
509 void set_glyph_data (const HBUINT24 glyph_data[])
510 {
511 match_glyph_data16 = nullptr;
512 match_glyph_data24 = glyph_data;
513 }
514#endif
515
516 void reset (unsigned int start_index_,
517 unsigned int num_items_)
518 {
519 idx = start_index_;
520 num_items = num_items_;
521 end = c->buffer->len;
522 matcher.set_syllable (start_index_ == c->buffer->idx ? c->buffer->cur().syllable () : 0);
523 }
524
525 void reject ()
526 {
527 num_items++;
528 backup_glyph_data ();
529 }
530
531 matcher_t::may_skip_t
532 may_skip (const hb_glyph_info_t &info) const
533 { return matcher.may_skip (c, info); }
534
535 enum match_t {
536 MATCH,
537 NOT_MATCH,
538 SKIP
539 };
540
541 match_t match (hb_glyph_info_t &info)
542 {
543 matcher_t::may_skip_t skip = matcher.may_skip (c, info);
544 if (unlikely (skip == matcher_t::SKIP_YES))
545 return SKIP;
546
547 matcher_t::may_match_t match = matcher.may_match (info, glyph_data: get_glyph_data ());
548 if (match == matcher_t::MATCH_YES ||
549 (match == matcher_t::MATCH_MAYBE &&
550 skip == matcher_t::SKIP_NO))
551 return MATCH;
552
553 if (skip == matcher_t::SKIP_NO)
554 return NOT_MATCH;
555
556 return SKIP;
557 }
558
559 bool next (unsigned *unsafe_to = nullptr)
560 {
561 assert (num_items > 0);
562 /* The alternate condition below is faster at string boundaries,
563 * but produces subpar "unsafe-to-concat" values. */
564 signed stop = (signed) end - (signed) num_items;
565 if (c->buffer->flags & HB_BUFFER_FLAG_PRODUCE_UNSAFE_TO_CONCAT)
566 stop = (signed) end - 1;
567 while ((signed) idx < stop)
568 {
569 idx++;
570 switch (match (info&: c->buffer->info[idx]))
571 {
572 case MATCH:
573 {
574 num_items--;
575 advance_glyph_data ();
576 return true;
577 }
578 case NOT_MATCH:
579 {
580 if (unsafe_to)
581 *unsafe_to = idx + 1;
582 return false;
583 }
584 case SKIP:
585 continue;
586 }
587 }
588 if (unsafe_to)
589 *unsafe_to = end;
590 return false;
591 }
592 bool prev (unsigned *unsafe_from = nullptr)
593 {
594 assert (num_items > 0);
595 /* The alternate condition below is faster at string boundaries,
596 * but produces subpar "unsafe-to-concat" values. */
597 unsigned stop = num_items - 1;
598 if (c->buffer->flags & HB_BUFFER_FLAG_PRODUCE_UNSAFE_TO_CONCAT)
599 stop = 1 - 1;
600 while (idx > stop)
601 {
602 idx--;
603 switch (match (info&: c->buffer->out_info[idx]))
604 {
605 case MATCH:
606 {
607 num_items--;
608 advance_glyph_data ();
609 return true;
610 }
611 case NOT_MATCH:
612 {
613 if (unsafe_from)
614 *unsafe_from = hb_max (1u, idx) - 1u;
615 return false;
616 }
617 case SKIP:
618 continue;
619 }
620 }
621 if (unsafe_from)
622 *unsafe_from = 0;
623 return false;
624 }
625
626 hb_codepoint_t
627 get_glyph_data ()
628 {
629 if (match_glyph_data16) return *match_glyph_data16;
630#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
631 else
632 if (match_glyph_data24) return *match_glyph_data24;
633#endif
634 return 0;
635 }
636 void
637 advance_glyph_data ()
638 {
639 if (match_glyph_data16) match_glyph_data16++;
640#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
641 else
642 if (match_glyph_data24) match_glyph_data24++;
643#endif
644 }
645 void
646 backup_glyph_data ()
647 {
648 if (match_glyph_data16) match_glyph_data16--;
649#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
650 else
651 if (match_glyph_data24) match_glyph_data24--;
652#endif
653 }
654
655 unsigned int idx;
656 protected:
657 hb_ot_apply_context_t *c;
658 matcher_t matcher;
659 const HBUINT16 *match_glyph_data16;
660#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
661 const HBUINT24 *match_glyph_data24;
662#endif
663
664 unsigned int num_items;
665 unsigned int end;
666 };

668
669 const char *get_name () { return "APPLY"; }
670 typedef return_t (*recurse_func_t) (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c, unsigned int lookup_index);
671 template <typename T>
672 return_t dispatch (const T &obj) { return obj.apply (this); }
673 static return_t default_return_value () { return false; }
674 bool stop_sublookup_iteration (return_t r) const { return r; }
675 return_t recurse (unsigned int sub_lookup_index)
676 {
677 if (unlikely (nesting_level_left == 0 || !recurse_func || buffer->max_ops-- <= 0))
678 {
679 buffer->shaping_failed = true;
680 return default_return_value ();
681 }
682
683 nesting_level_left--;
684 bool ret = recurse_func (this, sub_lookup_index);
685 nesting_level_left++;
686 return ret;
687 }

772 bool match_properties_mark (hb_codepoint_t glyph,
773 unsigned int glyph_props,
774 unsigned int match_props) const
775 {
776 /* If using mark filtering sets, the high short of
777 * match_props has the set index.
778 */
779 if (match_props & LookupFlag::UseMarkFilteringSet)
780 return gdef.mark_set_covers (set_index: match_props >> 16, glyph_id: glyph);
781
782 /* The second byte of match_props has the meaning
783 * "ignore marks of attachment type different than
784 * the attachment type specified."
785 */
786 if (match_props & LookupFlag::MarkAttachmentType)
787 return (match_props & LookupFlag::MarkAttachmentType) == (glyph_props & LookupFlag::MarkAttachmentType);
788
789 return true;
790 }
791
792 bool check_glyph_property (const hb_glyph_info_t *info,
793 unsigned int match_props) const
794 {
795 hb_codepoint_t glyph = info->codepoint;
796 unsigned int glyph_props = _hb_glyph_info_get_glyph_props (info);
797
798 /* Not covered, if, for example, glyph class is ligature and
799 * match_props includes LookupFlags::IgnoreLigatures
800 */
801 if (glyph_props & match_props & LookupFlag::IgnoreFlags)
802 return false;
803
804 if (unlikely (glyph_props & HB_OT_LAYOUT_GLYPH_PROPS_MARK))
805 return match_properties_mark (glyph, glyph_props, match_props);
806
807 return true;
808 }
809
810 void _set_glyph_class (hb_codepoint_t glyph_index,
811 unsigned int class_guess = 0,
812 bool ligature = false,
813 bool component = false)
814 {
815 digest.add (g: glyph_index);
816
817 if (new_syllables != (unsigned) -1)
818 buffer->cur().syllable() = new_syllables;
819
820 unsigned int props = _hb_glyph_info_get_glyph_props (info: &buffer->cur());
821 props |= HB_OT_LAYOUT_GLYPH_PROPS_SUBSTITUTED;
822 if (ligature)
823 {
824 props |= HB_OT_LAYOUT_GLYPH_PROPS_LIGATED;
825 /* In the only place that the MULTIPLIED bit is used, Uniscribe
826 * seems to only care about the "last" transformation between
827 * Ligature and Multiple substitutions. Ie. if you ligate, expand,
828 * and ligate again, it forgives the multiplication and acts as
829 * if only ligation happened. As such, clear MULTIPLIED bit.
830 */
831 props &= ~HB_OT_LAYOUT_GLYPH_PROPS_MULTIPLIED;
832 }
833 if (component)
834 props |= HB_OT_LAYOUT_GLYPH_PROPS_MULTIPLIED;
835 if (likely (has_glyph_classes))
836 {
837 props &= HB_OT_LAYOUT_GLYPH_PROPS_PRESERVE;
838 _hb_glyph_info_set_glyph_props (info: &buffer->cur(), props: props | gdef.get_glyph_props (glyph: glyph_index));
839 }
840 else if (class_guess)
841 {
842 props &= HB_OT_LAYOUT_GLYPH_PROPS_PRESERVE;
843 _hb_glyph_info_set_glyph_props (info: &buffer->cur(), props: props | class_guess);
844 }
845 else
846 _hb_glyph_info_set_glyph_props (info: &buffer->cur(), props);
847 }
848
849 void replace_glyph (hb_codepoint_t glyph_index)
850 {
851 _set_glyph_class (glyph_index);
852 (void) buffer->replace_glyph (glyph_index);
853 }
854 void replace_glyph_inplace (hb_codepoint_t glyph_index)
855 {
856 _set_glyph_class (glyph_index);
857 buffer->cur().codepoint = glyph_index;
858 }
859 void replace_glyph_with_ligature (hb_codepoint_t glyph_index,
860 unsigned int class_guess)
861 {
862 _set_glyph_class (glyph_index, class_guess, ligature: true);
863 (void) buffer->replace_glyph (glyph_index);
864 }
865 void output_glyph_for_component (hb_codepoint_t glyph_index,
866 unsigned int class_guess)
867 {
868 _set_glyph_class (glyph_index, class_guess, ligature: false, component: true);
869 (void) buffer->output_glyph (glyph_index);
870 }
871};

938 }

943 }

964#ifndef HB_NO_OT_LAYOUT_LOOKUP_CACHE
965 template <typename T>
966 auto cache_cost (const T &obj, hb_priority<1>) HB_AUTO_RETURN ( obj.cache_cost () )
967 template <typename T>
968 auto cache_cost (const T &obj, hb_priority<0>) HB_AUTO_RETURN ( 0u )
969#endif
970
971 /* Dispatch interface. */
972 template <typename T>
973 return_t dispatch (const T &obj)
974 {
975 hb_applicable_t *entry = &array[i++];
976
977 entry->init (obj,
978 apply_to<T>
979#ifndef HB_NO_OT_LAYOUT_LOOKUP_CACHE
980 , apply_cached_to<T>
981 , cache_func_to<T>
982#endif
983 );
984
985#ifndef HB_NO_OT_LAYOUT_LOOKUP_CACHE
986 /* Cache handling
987 *
988 * We allow one subtable from each lookup to use a cache. The assumption
989 * being that multiple subtables of the same lookup cannot use a cache
990 * because the resources they would use will collide. As such, we ask
991 * each subtable to tell us how much it costs (which a cache would avoid),
992 * and we allocate the cache opportunity to the costliest subtable.
993 */
994 unsigned cost = cache_cost (obj, hb_prioritize);
995 if (cost > cache_user_cost)
996 {
997 cache_user_idx = i - 1;
998 cache_user_cost = cost;
999 }
1000#endif
1001
1002 return hb_empty_t ();
1003 }
1004 static return_t default_return_value () { return hb_empty_t (); }
1005
1006 hb_accelerate_subtables_context_t (hb_applicable_t *array_) :
1007 array (array_) {}
1008
1009 hb_applicable_t *array;
1010 unsigned i = 0;
1011
1012#ifndef HB_NO_OT_LAYOUT_LOOKUP_CACHE
1013 unsigned cache_user_idx = (unsigned) -1;
1014 unsigned cache_user_cost = 0;
1015#endif
1016};

1047static inline bool intersects_class (const hb_set_t *glyphs, unsigned value, const void *data, void *cache)
1048{
1049 const ClassDef &class_def = *reinterpret_cast<const ClassDef *>(data);
1050 hb_map_t *map = (hb_map_t *) cache;
1051
1052 hb_codepoint_t *cached_v;
1053 if (map->has (key: value, vp: &cached_v))
1054 return *cached_v;
1055
1056 bool v = class_def.intersects_class (glyphs, klass: value);
1057 map->set (key: value, value&: v);
1058
1059 return v;
1060}

1177template <typename HBUINT>
1178static inline bool would_match_input (hb_would_apply_context_t *c,
1179 unsigned int count, /* Including the first glyph (not matched) */
1180 const HBUINT input[], /* Array of input values--start with second glyph */
1181 match_func_t match_func,
1182 const void *match_data)
1183{
1184 if (count != c->len)
1185 return false;
1186
1187 for (unsigned int i = 1; i < count; i++)
1188 {
1189 hb_glyph_info_t info;
1190 info.codepoint = c->glyphs[i];
1191 if (likely (!match_func (info, input[i - 1], match_data)))
1192 return false;
1193 }

1197template <typename HBUINT>
1198static inline bool match_input (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c,
1199 unsigned int count, /* Including the first glyph (not matched) */
1200 const HBUINT input[], /* Array of input values--start with second glyph */
1201 match_func_t match_func,
1202 const void *match_data,
1203 unsigned int *end_position,
1204 unsigned int match_positions[HB_MAX_CONTEXT_LENGTH],
1205 unsigned int *p_total_component_count = nullptr)
1206{
1207 TRACE_APPLY (nullptr);
1208
1209 if (unlikely (count > HB_MAX_CONTEXT_LENGTH)) return_trace (false);
1210
1211 hb_buffer_t *buffer = c->buffer;
1212
1213 hb_ot_apply_context_t::skipping_iterator_t &skippy_iter = c->iter_input;
1214 skippy_iter.reset (start_index_: buffer->idx, num_items_: count - 1);
1215 skippy_iter.set_match_func (match_func_: match_func, match_data_: match_data);
1216 skippy_iter.set_glyph_data (input);
1217
1218 /*
1219 * This is perhaps the trickiest part of OpenType... Remarks:
1220 *
1221 * - If all components of the ligature were marks, we call this a mark ligature.
1222 *
1223 * - If there is no GDEF, and the ligature is NOT a mark ligature, we categorize
1224 * it as a ligature glyph.
1225 *
1226 * - Ligatures cannot be formed across glyphs attached to different components
1227 * of previous ligatures. Eg. the sequence is LAM,SHADDA,LAM,FATHA,HEH, and
1228 * LAM,LAM,HEH form a ligature, leaving SHADDA,FATHA next to eachother.
1229 * However, it would be wrong to ligate that SHADDA,FATHA sequence.
1230 * There are a couple of exceptions to this:
1231 *
1232 * o If a ligature tries ligating with marks that belong to it itself, go ahead,
1233 * assuming that the font designer knows what they are doing (otherwise it can
1234 * break Indic stuff when a matra wants to ligate with a conjunct,
1235 *
1236 * o If two marks want to ligate and they belong to different components of the
1237 * same ligature glyph, and said ligature glyph is to be ignored according to
1238 * mark-filtering rules, then allow.
1239 * https://github.com/harfbuzz/harfbuzz/issues/545
1240 */
1241
1242 unsigned int total_component_count = 0;
1243 total_component_count += _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_num_comps (info: &buffer->cur());
1244
1245 unsigned int first_lig_id = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_id (info: &buffer->cur());
1246 unsigned int first_lig_comp = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_comp (info: &buffer->cur());
1247
1248 enum {
1249 LIGBASE_NOT_CHECKED,
1250 LIGBASE_MAY_NOT_SKIP,
1251 LIGBASE_MAY_SKIP
1252 } ligbase = LIGBASE_NOT_CHECKED;
1253
1254 match_positions[0] = buffer->idx;
1255 for (unsigned int i = 1; i < count; i++)
1256 {
1257 unsigned unsafe_to;
1258 if (!skippy_iter.next (unsafe_to: &unsafe_to))
1259 {
1260 *end_position = unsafe_to;
1261 return_trace (false);
1262 }
1263
1264 match_positions[i] = skippy_iter.idx;
1265
1266 unsigned int this_lig_id = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_id (info: &buffer->info[skippy_iter.idx]);
1267 unsigned int this_lig_comp = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_comp (info: &buffer->info[skippy_iter.idx]);
1268
1269 if (first_lig_id && first_lig_comp)
1270 {
1271 /* If first component was attached to a previous ligature component,
1272 * all subsequent components should be attached to the same ligature
1273 * component, otherwise we shouldn't ligate them... */
1274 if (first_lig_id != this_lig_id || first_lig_comp != this_lig_comp)
1275 {
1276 /* ...unless, we are attached to a base ligature and that base
1277 * ligature is ignorable. */
1278 if (ligbase == LIGBASE_NOT_CHECKED)
1279 {
1280 bool found = false;
1281 const auto *out = buffer->out_info;
1282 unsigned int j = buffer->out_len;
1283 while (j && _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_id (info: &out[j - 1]) == first_lig_id)
1284 {
1285 if (_hb_glyph_info_get_lig_comp (info: &out[j - 1]) == 0)
1286 {
1287 j--;
1288 found = true;
1289 break;
1290 }
1291 j--;
1292 }
1293
1294 if (found && skippy_iter.may_skip (info: out[j]) == hb_ot_apply_context_t::matcher_t::SKIP_YES)
1295 ligbase = LIGBASE_MAY_SKIP;
1296 else
1297 ligbase = LIGBASE_MAY_NOT_SKIP;
1298 }
1299
1300 if (ligbase == LIGBASE_MAY_NOT_SKIP)
1301 return_trace (false);
1302 }
1303 }
1304 else
1305 {
1306 /* If first component was NOT attached to a previous ligature component,
1307 * all subsequent components should also NOT be attached to any ligature
1308 * component, unless they are attached to the first component itself! */
1309 if (this_lig_id && this_lig_comp && (this_lig_id != first_lig_id))
1310 return_trace (false);
1311 }
1312
1313 total_component_count += _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_num_comps (info: &buffer->info[skippy_iter.idx]);
1314 }
1315
1316 *end_position = skippy_iter.idx + 1;
1317
1318 if (p_total_component_count)
1319 *p_total_component_count = total_component_count;
1320
1321 return_trace (true);
1322}
1323static inline bool ligate_input (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c,
1324 unsigned int count, /* Including the first glyph */
1325 const unsigned int match_positions[HB_MAX_CONTEXT_LENGTH], /* Including the first glyph */
1326 unsigned int match_end,
1327 hb_codepoint_t lig_glyph,
1328 unsigned int total_component_count)
1329{
1330 TRACE_APPLY (nullptr);
1331
1332 hb_buffer_t *buffer = c->buffer;
1333
1334 buffer->merge_clusters (start: buffer->idx, end: match_end);
1335
1336 /* - If a base and one or more marks ligate, consider that as a base, NOT
1337 * ligature, such that all following marks can still attach to it.
1338 * https://github.com/harfbuzz/harfbuzz/issues/1109
1339 *
1340 * - If all components of the ligature were marks, we call this a mark ligature.
1341 * If it *is* a mark ligature, we don't allocate a new ligature id, and leave
1342 * the ligature to keep its old ligature id. This will allow it to attach to
1343 * a base ligature in GPOS. Eg. if the sequence is: LAM,LAM,SHADDA,FATHA,HEH,
1344 * and LAM,LAM,HEH for a ligature, they will leave SHADDA and FATHA with a
1345 * ligature id and component value of 2. Then if SHADDA,FATHA form a ligature
1346 * later, we don't want them to lose their ligature id/component, otherwise
1347 * GPOS will fail to correctly position the mark ligature on top of the
1348 * LAM,LAM,HEH ligature. See:
1349 * https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=676343
1350 *
1351 * - If a ligature is formed of components that some of which are also ligatures
1352 * themselves, and those ligature components had marks attached to *their*
1353 * components, we have to attach the marks to the new ligature component
1354 * positions! Now *that*'s tricky! And these marks may be following the
1355 * last component of the whole sequence, so we should loop forward looking
1356 * for them and update them.
1357 *
1358 * Eg. the sequence is LAM,LAM,SHADDA,FATHA,HEH, and the font first forms a
1359 * 'calt' ligature of LAM,HEH, leaving the SHADDA and FATHA with a ligature
1360 * id and component == 1. Now, during 'liga', the LAM and the LAM-HEH ligature
1361 * form a LAM-LAM-HEH ligature. We need to reassign the SHADDA and FATHA to
1362 * the new ligature with a component value of 2.
1363 *
1364 * This in fact happened to a font... See:
1365 * https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=437633
1366 */
1367
1368 bool is_base_ligature = _hb_glyph_info_is_base_glyph (info: &buffer->info[match_positions[0]]);
1369 bool is_mark_ligature = _hb_glyph_info_is_mark (info: &buffer->info[match_positions[0]]);
1370 for (unsigned int i = 1; i < count; i++)
1371 if (!_hb_glyph_info_is_mark (info: &buffer->info[match_positions[i]]))
1372 {
1373 is_base_ligature = false;
1374 is_mark_ligature = false;
1375 break;
1376 }
1377 bool is_ligature = !is_base_ligature && !is_mark_ligature;
1378
1379 unsigned int klass = is_ligature ? HB_OT_LAYOUT_GLYPH_PROPS_LIGATURE : 0;
1380 unsigned int lig_id = is_ligature ? _hb_allocate_lig_id (buffer) : 0;
1381 unsigned int last_lig_id = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_id (info: &buffer->cur());
1382 unsigned int last_num_components = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_num_comps (info: &buffer->cur());
1383 unsigned int components_so_far = last_num_components;
1384
1385 if (is_ligature)
1386 {
1387 _hb_glyph_info_set_lig_props_for_ligature (info: &buffer->cur(), lig_id, lig_num_comps: total_component_count);
1388 if (_hb_glyph_info_get_general_category (info: &buffer->cur()) == HB_UNICODE_GENERAL_CATEGORY_NON_SPACING_MARK)
1389 {
1390 _hb_glyph_info_set_general_category (info: &buffer->cur(), gen_cat: HB_UNICODE_GENERAL_CATEGORY_OTHER_LETTER);
1391 }
1392 }
1393 c->replace_glyph_with_ligature (glyph_index: lig_glyph, class_guess: klass);
1394
1395 for (unsigned int i = 1; i < count; i++)
1396 {
1397 while (buffer->idx < match_positions[i] && buffer->successful)
1398 {
1399 if (is_ligature)
1400 {
1401 unsigned int this_comp = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_comp (info: &buffer->cur());
1402 if (this_comp == 0)
1403 this_comp = last_num_components;
1404 unsigned int new_lig_comp = components_so_far - last_num_components +
1405 hb_min (this_comp, last_num_components);
1406 _hb_glyph_info_set_lig_props_for_mark (info: &buffer->cur(), lig_id, lig_comp: new_lig_comp);
1407 }
1408 (void) buffer->next_glyph ();
1409 }
1410
1411 last_lig_id = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_id (info: &buffer->cur());
1412 last_num_components = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_num_comps (info: &buffer->cur());
1413 components_so_far += last_num_components;
1414
1415 /* Skip the base glyph */
1416 buffer->idx++;
1417 }
1418
1419 if (!is_mark_ligature && last_lig_id)
1420 {
1421 /* Re-adjust components for any marks following. */
1422 for (unsigned i = buffer->idx; i < buffer->len; ++i)
1423 {
1424 if (last_lig_id != _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_id (info: &buffer->info[i])) break;
1425
1426 unsigned this_comp = _hb_glyph_info_get_lig_comp (info: &buffer->info[i]);
1427 if (!this_comp) break;
1428
1429 unsigned new_lig_comp = components_so_far - last_num_components +
1430 hb_min (this_comp, last_num_components);
1431 _hb_glyph_info_set_lig_props_for_mark (info: &buffer->info[i], lig_id, lig_comp: new_lig_comp);
1432 }
1433 }
1434 return_trace (true);
1435}

1437template <typename HBUINT>
1438static inline bool match_backtrack (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c,
1439 unsigned int count,
1440 const HBUINT backtrack[],
1441 match_func_t match_func,
1442 const void *match_data,
1443 unsigned int *match_start)
1444{
1445 TRACE_APPLY (nullptr);
1446
1447 hb_ot_apply_context_t::skipping_iterator_t &skippy_iter = c->iter_context;
1448 skippy_iter.reset (start_index_: c->buffer->backtrack_len (), num_items_: count);
1449 skippy_iter.set_match_func (match_func_: match_func, match_data_: match_data);
1450 skippy_iter.set_glyph_data (backtrack);
1451
1452 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
1453 {
1454 unsigned unsafe_from;
1455 if (!skippy_iter.prev (unsafe_from: &unsafe_from))
1456 {
1457 *match_start = unsafe_from;
1458 return_trace (false);
1459 }
1460 }
1461
1462 *match_start = skippy_iter.idx;
1463 return_trace (true);
1464}

1466template <typename HBUINT>
1467static inline bool match_lookahead (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c,
1468 unsigned int count,
1469 const HBUINT lookahead[],
1470 match_func_t match_func,
1471 const void *match_data,
1472 unsigned int start_index,
1473 unsigned int *end_index)
1474{
1475 TRACE_APPLY (nullptr);
1476
1477 hb_ot_apply_context_t::skipping_iterator_t &skippy_iter = c->iter_context;
1478 skippy_iter.reset (start_index_: start_index - 1, num_items_: count);
1479 skippy_iter.set_match_func (match_func_: match_func, match_data_: match_data);
1480 skippy_iter.set_glyph_data (lookahead);
1481
1482 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
1483 {
1484 unsigned unsafe_to;
1485 if (!skippy_iter.next (unsafe_to: &unsafe_to))
1486 {
1487 *end_index = unsafe_to;
1488 return_trace (false);
1489 }
1490 }
1491
1492 *end_index = skippy_iter.idx + 1;
1493 return_trace (true);
1494}

1498struct LookupRecord
1499{
1500 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
1501 const hb_map_t *lookup_map) const
1502 {
1503 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
1504 auto *out = c->embed (obj: *this);
1505 if (unlikely (!out)) return_trace (false);
1506
1507 return_trace (c->check_assign (out->lookupListIndex, lookup_map->get (lookupListIndex), HB_SERIALIZE_ERROR_INT_OVERFLOW));
1508 }
1509
1510 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
1511 {
1512 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
1513 return_trace (c->check_struct (this));
1514 }
1515
1516 HBUINT16 sequenceIndex; /* Index into current glyph
1517 * sequence--first glyph = 0 */
1518 HBUINT16 lookupListIndex; /* Lookup to apply to that
1519 * position--zero--based */
1520 public:
1521 DEFINE_SIZE_STATIC (4);
1522};

1524static unsigned serialize_lookuprecord_array (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
1525 const hb_array_t<const LookupRecord> lookupRecords,
1526 const hb_map_t *lookup_map)
1527{

1529 for (const LookupRecord& r : lookupRecords)
1530 {
1531 if (!lookup_map->has (key: r.lookupListIndex))

1535 return 0;

1538 }

1542enum ContextFormat { SimpleContext = 1, ClassBasedContext = 2, CoverageBasedContext = 3 };
1543
1544template <typename HBUINT>
1545static void context_closure_recurse_lookups (hb_closure_context_t *c,
1546 unsigned inputCount, const HBUINT input[],
1547 unsigned lookupCount,
1548 const LookupRecord lookupRecord[] /* Array of LookupRecords--in design order */,
1549 unsigned value,
1550 ContextFormat context_format,
1551 const void *data,
1552 intersected_glyphs_func_t intersected_glyphs_func,
1553 void *cache)
1554{
1555 hb_set_t covered_seq_indicies;
1556 hb_set_t pos_glyphs;
1557 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < lookupCount; i++)
1558 {
1559 unsigned seqIndex = lookupRecord[i].sequenceIndex;
1560 if (seqIndex >= inputCount) continue;
1561
1562 bool has_pos_glyphs = false;
1563
1564 if (!covered_seq_indicies.has (k: seqIndex))
1565 {
1566 has_pos_glyphs = true;
1567 pos_glyphs.clear ();
1568 if (seqIndex == 0)
1569 {
1570 switch (context_format) {
1571 case ContextFormat::SimpleContext:
1572 pos_glyphs.add (g: value);
1573 break;
1574 case ContextFormat::ClassBasedContext:
1575 intersected_glyphs_func (&c->parent_active_glyphs (), data, value, &pos_glyphs, cache);
1576 break;
1577 case ContextFormat::CoverageBasedContext:
1578 pos_glyphs.set (c->parent_active_glyphs ());
1579 break;
1580 }
1581 }
1582 else
1583 {
1584 const void *input_data = input;
1585 unsigned input_value = seqIndex - 1;
1586 if (context_format != ContextFormat::SimpleContext)
1587 {
1588 input_data = data;
1589 input_value = input[seqIndex - 1];
1590 }
1591
1592 intersected_glyphs_func (c->glyphs, input_data, input_value, &pos_glyphs, cache);
1593 }
1594 }
1595
1596 covered_seq_indicies.add (g: seqIndex);
1597 if (has_pos_glyphs) {
1598 c->push_cur_active_glyphs () = std::move (pos_glyphs);
1599 } else {
1600 c->push_cur_active_glyphs ().set (*c->glyphs);
1601 }
1602
1603 unsigned endIndex = inputCount;
1604 if (context_format == ContextFormat::CoverageBasedContext)
1605 endIndex += 1;
1606
1607 c->recurse (lookup_index: lookupRecord[i].lookupListIndex, covered_seq_indicies: &covered_seq_indicies, seq_index: seqIndex, end_index: endIndex);
1608
1609 c->pop_cur_done_glyphs ();
1610 }
1611}

1613template <typename context_t>
1614static inline void recurse_lookups (context_t *c,
1615 unsigned int lookupCount,
1616 const LookupRecord lookupRecord[] /* Array of LookupRecords--in design order */)
1617{
1618 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < lookupCount; i++)
1619 c->recurse (lookupRecord[i].lookupListIndex);
1620}

1622static inline void apply_lookup (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c,
1623 unsigned int count, /* Including the first glyph */
1624 unsigned int match_positions[HB_MAX_CONTEXT_LENGTH], /* Including the first glyph */
1625 unsigned int lookupCount,
1626 const LookupRecord lookupRecord[], /* Array of LookupRecords--in design order */
1627 unsigned int match_end)
1628{
1629 hb_buffer_t *buffer = c->buffer;
1630 int end;
1631
1632 /* All positions are distance from beginning of *output* buffer.
1633 * Adjust. */
1634 {
1635 unsigned int bl = buffer->backtrack_len ();
1636 end = bl + match_end - buffer->idx;
1637
1638 int delta = bl - buffer->idx;
1639 /* Convert positions to new indexing. */
1640 for (unsigned int j = 0; j < count; j++)
1641 match_positions[j] += delta;
1642 }
1643
1644 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < lookupCount && buffer->successful; i++)
1645 {
1646 unsigned int idx = lookupRecord[i].sequenceIndex;
1647 if (idx >= count)
1648 continue;
1649
1650 unsigned int orig_len = buffer->backtrack_len () + buffer->lookahead_len ();
1651
1652 /* This can happen if earlier recursed lookups deleted many entries. */
1653 if (unlikely (match_positions[idx] >= orig_len))
1654 continue;
1655
1656 if (unlikely (!buffer->move_to (match_positions[idx])))
1657 break;
1658
1659 if (unlikely (buffer->max_ops <= 0))
1660 break;
1661
1662 if (HB_BUFFER_MESSAGE_MORE && c->buffer->messaging ())
1663 {
1664 if (buffer->have_output)
1665 c->buffer->sync_so_far ();
1666 c->buffer->message (font: c->font,
1667 fmt: "recursing to lookup %u at %u",
1668 (unsigned) lookupRecord[i].lookupListIndex,
1669 buffer->idx);
1670 }
1671
1672 if (!c->recurse (sub_lookup_index: lookupRecord[i].lookupListIndex))
1673 continue;
1674
1675 if (HB_BUFFER_MESSAGE_MORE && c->buffer->messaging ())
1676 {
1677 if (buffer->have_output)
1678 c->buffer->sync_so_far ();
1679 c->buffer->message (font: c->font,
1680 fmt: "recursed to lookup %u",
1681 (unsigned) lookupRecord[i].lookupListIndex);
1682 }
1683
1684 unsigned int new_len = buffer->backtrack_len () + buffer->lookahead_len ();
1685 int delta = new_len - orig_len;
1686
1687 if (!delta)
1688 continue;
1689
1690 /* Recursed lookup changed buffer len. Adjust.
1691 *
1692 * TODO:
1693 *
1694 * Right now, if buffer length increased by n, we assume n new glyphs
1695 * were added right after the current position, and if buffer length
1696 * was decreased by n, we assume n match positions after the current
1697 * one where removed. The former (buffer length increased) case is
1698 * fine, but the decrease case can be improved in at least two ways,
1699 * both of which are significant:
1700 *
1701 * - If recursed-to lookup is MultipleSubst and buffer length
1702 * decreased, then it's current match position that was deleted,
1703 * NOT the one after it.
1704 *
1705 * - If buffer length was decreased by n, it does not necessarily
1706 * mean that n match positions where removed, as there recursed-to
1707 * lookup might had a different LookupFlag. Here's a constructed
1708 * case of that:
1709 * https://github.com/harfbuzz/harfbuzz/discussions/3538
1710 *
1711 * It should be possible to construct tests for both of these cases.
1712 */
1713
1714 end += delta;
1715 if (end < int (match_positions[idx]))
1716 {
1717 /* End might end up being smaller than match_positions[idx] if the recursed
1718 * lookup ended up removing many items.
1719 * Just never rewind end beyond start of current position, since that is
1720 * not possible in the recursed lookup. Also adjust delta as such.
1721 *
1722 * https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=659496
1723 * https://github.com/harfbuzz/harfbuzz/issues/1611
1724 */
1725 delta += match_positions[idx] - end;
1726 end = match_positions[idx];
1727 }
1728
1729 unsigned int next = idx + 1; /* next now is the position after the recursed lookup. */
1730
1731 if (delta > 0)
1732 {
1733 if (unlikely (delta + count > HB_MAX_CONTEXT_LENGTH))
1734 break;
1735 }
1736 else
1737 {
1738 /* NOTE: delta is non-positive. */
1739 delta = hb_max (delta, (int) next - (int) count);
1740 next -= delta;
1741 }
1742
1743 /* Shift! */
1744 memmove (dest: match_positions + next + delta, src: match_positions + next,
1745 n: (count - next) * sizeof (match_positions[0]));
1746 next += delta;
1747 count += delta;
1748
1749 /* Fill in new entries. */
1750 for (unsigned int j = idx + 1; j < next; j++)
1751 match_positions[j] = match_positions[j - 1] + 1;
1752
1753 /* And fixup the rest. */
1754 for (; next < count; next++)
1755 match_positions[next] += delta;
1756 }
1757
1758 (void) buffer->move_to (i: end);
1759}

1911 void collect_glyphs (hb_collect_glyphs_context_t *c,
1912 ContextCollectGlyphsLookupContext &lookup_context) const

3805 hb_requires (hb_is_iterator (Iterator))>
3806 bool serialize_coverage_offsets (hb_subset_context_t *c, Iterator it, const void* base) const
3807 {
3808 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);

4030struct hb_ot_layout_lookup_accelerator_t
4031{
4032 template <typename TLookup>
4033 static hb_ot_layout_lookup_accelerator_t *create (const TLookup &lookup)
4034 {
4035 unsigned count = lookup.get_subtable_count ();
4036
4037 unsigned size = sizeof (hb_ot_layout_lookup_accelerator_t) -
4038 HB_VAR_ARRAY * sizeof (hb_accelerate_subtables_context_t::hb_applicable_t) +
4039 count * sizeof (hb_accelerate_subtables_context_t::hb_applicable_t);
4040
4041 /* The following is a calloc because when we are collecting subtables,
4042 * some of them might be invalid and hence not collect; as a result,
4043 * we might not fill in all the count entries of the subtables array.
4044 * Zeroing it allows the set digest to gatekeep it without having to
4045 * initialize it further. */
4046 auto *thiz = (hb_ot_layout_lookup_accelerator_t *) hb_calloc (nmemb: 1, size: size);
4047 if (unlikely (!thiz))
4048 return nullptr;
4049
4050 hb_accelerate_subtables_context_t c_accelerate_subtables (thiz->subtables);
4051 lookup.dispatch (&c_accelerate_subtables);
4052
4053 thiz->digest.init ();
4054 for (auto& subtable : hb_iter (thiz->subtables, count))
4055 thiz->digest.add (o: subtable.digest);
4056
4057#ifndef HB_NO_OT_LAYOUT_LOOKUP_CACHE
4058 thiz->cache_user_idx = c_accelerate_subtables.cache_user_idx;
4059 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; i++)
4060 if (i != thiz->cache_user_idx)
4061 thiz->subtables[i].apply_cached_func = thiz->subtables[i].apply_func;
4062#endif
4063
4064 return thiz;
4065 }
4066
4067 bool may_have (hb_codepoint_t g) const
4068 { return digest.may_have (g); }
4069
4070 bool apply (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c, unsigned subtables_count, bool use_cache) const
4071 {
4072#ifndef HB_NO_OT_LAYOUT_LOOKUP_CACHE
4073 if (use_cache)
4074 {
4075 return
4076 + hb_iter (hb_iter (subtables, subtables_count))
4077 | hb_map ([&c] (const hb_accelerate_subtables_context_t::hb_applicable_t &_) { return _.apply_cached (c); })
4078 | hb_any
4079 ;
4080 }
4081 else
4082#endif
4083 {
4084 return
4085 + hb_iter (hb_iter (subtables, subtables_count))
4086 | hb_map ([&c] (const hb_accelerate_subtables_context_t::hb_applicable_t &_) { return _.apply (c); })
4087 | hb_any
4088 ;
4089 }
4090 return false;
4091 }
4092
4093 bool cache_enter (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c) const
4094 {
4095#ifndef HB_NO_OT_LAYOUT_LOOKUP_CACHE
4096 return cache_user_idx != (unsigned) -1 &&
4097 subtables[cache_user_idx].cache_enter (c);
4098#else
4099 return false;
4100#endif
4101 }
4102 void cache_leave (hb_ot_apply_context_t *c) const
4103 {
4104#ifndef HB_NO_OT_LAYOUT_LOOKUP_CACHE
4105 subtables[cache_user_idx].cache_leave (c);
4106#endif
4107 }
4108
4109
4110 hb_set_digest_t digest;
4111 private:
4112#ifndef HB_NO_OT_LAYOUT_LOOKUP_CACHE
4113 unsigned cache_user_idx = (unsigned) -1;
4114#endif

4421 {
4422#ifndef HB_NO_VAR

4424 // if the FeatureVariation's table and the alternate version(s) intersect the
4425 // set of lookup indices.
4426 hb_set_t alternate_feature_indices;
4427 get_feature_variations ().closure_features (lookup_indexes: lookup_indices, feature_record_cond_idx_map, feature_indexes: &alternate_feature_indices);
4428 if (unlikely (alternate_feature_indices.in_error()))
4429 {
4430 feature_indices->err ();
4431 return;
4432 }
4433#endif
4434
4435 for (unsigned i : hb_iter (feature_indices))
4436 {
4437 hb_tag_t tag = get_feature_tag (i);
4438 if (tag == HB_TAG ('p', 'r', 'e', 'f'))
4439 // Note: Never ever drop feature 'pref', even if it's empty.
4440 // HarfBuzz chooses shaper for Khmer based on presence of this
4441 // feature. See thread at:
4442 // http://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/harfbuzz/2012-November/002660.html
4443 continue;
4444
4445
4446 const Feature *f = &(get_feature (i));
4447 const Feature** p = nullptr;
4448 if (feature_substitutes_map->has (key: i, vp: &p))
4449 f = *p;
4450
4451 if (!f->featureParams.is_null () &&
4452 tag == HB_TAG ('s', 'i', 'z', 'e'))
4453 continue;
4454
4455 if (!f->intersects_lookup_indexes (lookup_indexes: lookup_indices)
4456#ifndef HB_NO_VAR
4457 && !alternate_feature_indices.has (k: i)
4458#endif
4459 )

4465 struct accelerator_t
4466 {
4467 accelerator_t (hb_face_t *face)
4468 {
4469 this->table = hb_sanitize_context_t ().reference_table<T> (face);
4470 if (unlikely (this->table->is_blocklisted (this->table.get_blob (), face)))
4471 {
4472 hb_blob_destroy (this->table.get_blob ());
4473 this->table = hb_blob_get_empty ();
4474 }
4475
4476 this->lookup_count = table->get_lookup_count ();
4477
4478 this->accels = (hb_atomic_ptr_t<hb_ot_layout_lookup_accelerator_t> *) hb_calloc (this->lookup_count, sizeof (*accels));
4479 if (unlikely (!this->accels))
4480 {
4481 this->lookup_count = 0;
4482 this->table.destroy ();
4483 this->table = hb_blob_get_empty ();
4484 }
4485 }
4486 ~accelerator_t ()
4487 {
4488 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < this->lookup_count; i++)
4489 hb_free (this->accels[i]);
4490 hb_free (this->accels);
4491 this->table.destroy ();
4492 }

4494 hb_ot_layout_lookup_accelerator_t *get_accel (unsigned lookup_index) const
4495 {
4496 if (unlikely (lookup_index >= lookup_count)) return nullptr;
4497
4498 retry:
4499 auto *accel = accels[lookup_index].get_acquire ();
4500 if (unlikely (!accel))
4501 {
4502 accel = hb_ot_layout_lookup_accelerator_t::create (table->get_lookup (lookup_index));
4503 if (unlikely (!accel))
4504 return nullptr;
4505
4506 if (unlikely (!accels[lookup_index].cmpexch (nullptr, accel)))
4507 {
4508 hb_free (ptr: accel);
4509 goto retry;
4510 }
4511 }
4512
4513 return accel;
4514 }
